\f0\b\fs56 \cf0 Spinach Salad with Balsamic Dressing\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl240\ql\qnatural

\f1\fs36 \cf2 Serves:  
\b0 \cf0 4 servings\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs42 \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl400\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs40 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}1 shallot\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 tablespoons aged balsamic vinegar\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 teaspoon superfine sugar\
{\listtext	\'95	}Juice of 1/2 lemon\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 1/2 cups white mushrooms, sliced\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 to 3 cups spinach leaves\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 cup fresh basil leaves\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 cup sliced almonds, toasted\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 cup dried cranberries\
{\listtext	\'95	}4 to 5 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil (EVOO)\
{\listtext	\'95	}Salt and freshly ground pepper\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs42 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs40 \cf0 Chop the shallot and put it in a small bowl. Add the vinegar, sugar and lemon juice and set aside.\
Place spinach and basil in a serving bowl.  Add mushrooms, dried cranberries and sliced almonds.\
Whisk the EVOO into the vinegar mixture and season with salt and pepper. Toss the salad with the dressing and season with salt and pepper.\
